JAPAN DAYBOOK: Bank of Japan to Raise Inflation Forecast

-- B y   S t e v e n   M c P h e r s o n
-- 
2011-04-18T20:59:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/japan-daybook-bank-of-japan-to-raise-inflation-forecast.html
The  Bank of Japan  will raise its
inflation forecast in an April 28 report, people familiar with
the bank said.  WHAT TO WATCH
*S&P says U.S. AAA rating outlook “negative;” stocks, dollar
 drop, gold touches record
*U.S. Treasuries rise as stocks fall, speculation grows that
  Greece  will default
*Bank of  Japan  to raise FY12 inflation forecast to 0.5% from
 0.3% in April 28 report, four people familiar say
*Toshiba FY net income probably 130b yen, Nikkei says; company
 est. 100b, analysts 90b
*Mori Seiki to announce China venture today with Gildemeister,
 Shenyang Machine Tool, Nikkei says
*Google, Itochu, Sumitomo invest $500m in $2b General Electric
 Shepherds Flat wind project
*Sony decides against raising stake in liquid-crystal
 display venture with Sharp, Nikkei says; Sony had planned to
 raise stake as high as 34% from 7%  ECONOMY
*2pm  consumer confidence  for March
*3pm machine tool orders for March, revised  GOVERNMENT
